"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800744","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>As part of the Government Secure Intranet (GSI) network, emails sent to the Department for Education (DfE) from outside of the department are processed via a third party email filtering system, which provides antiviral and antispam capabilities. DfE can only comment on the mail flow process once it has entered the GSI network and can only comment on emails received by ministers via their departmental email address.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800744/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T16:55:04.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800744/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800744/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Department for Education: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether electronic communications from hon. Members to Ministers of her Department are passed through any third parties before they reach their recipient.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","117365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800745","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-12","<p>Electronic communications are passed across the internet via internet service providers. The routing of an email between a hon. Member and the Ministry of Defence (MOD) will pass through MOD networks.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800745/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T17:42:48.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800745/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800745/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-04","Ministry of Defence: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether electronic communications from hon. Members to Ministers of his Department are passed through any third parties before they reach their recipient.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","117366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800746","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-11","<p>It is plausible that some members use a 3<sup>rd</sup> party email account (eg Gmail) which will pass through the internet (multiple providers), the email then traverses the secure PSN (Public Service Network) which is supplied by a third party provider (Vodafone) under a cross government framework managed by the Cabinet Office. From there it will be routed directly into the DWP e-mail service which is part of a managed service with the third party provider DXC (formerly HPE).</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800746/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-11T17:52:49.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800746/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800746/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-04","Department for Work and Pensions: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether electronic communications from hon. Members to Ministers of his Department are passed through any third parties before they reach their recipient.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","117367"
