"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800756","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-12","<p>Belarus is a source, transit and destination country for individuals subjected to sex trafficking and forced labour. Our Embassy in Minsk has provided £100,000 of project funding to support the implementation of Council of Europe and UN recommendations on preventing human trafficking and gender inequality.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800756/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T13:19:24.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800756/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800756/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-04","Belarus: Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the extent of human trafficking in Belarus.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","117377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800757","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Secretary of State set out the Government’s position in a Written Ministerial Statement on 23 November:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2017-11-23/HCWS267/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2017-11-23/HCWS267/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800757/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:51:43.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800757/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800757/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-04","Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to give animal sentience protection under the law; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","117378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800758","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>Belarus is a source, transit and destination country for individuals subjected to sex trafficking and forced labour. Our Embassy in Minsk has provided £100,000 of project funding to support the implementation of Council of Europe and UN recommendations on preventing human trafficking and gender inequality.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800758/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:08:11.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800758/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800758/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-04","Belarus: Forced Labour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has assessed the extent to which forced labour is used in Belarus.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","117379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800759","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-07","<p>We are committed to ensuring that all children and young people, particularly those who are currently least active or from under-represented groups, have the best opportunities to engage in sport and physical activity. We are continuing to invest over £17 million annually in the School Games to ensure that children of all abilities are able to access high quality organised sport.</p><p> </p><p>Sport England is planning to invest £28m into Satellite Clubs between 2017-2021 to provide children and young people with opportunities to take part in sport outside of curriculum time. And through its new Families Fund, Sport England will be investing up to £40m into projects, which offer new opportunities for families with children to get active and play sport together. Sport England will also invest up to £3 million of National Lottery money through its new Potentials Fund which will support projects for young people (from ages 10 to 20) involved in social action and volunteering using sport and physical activity. This campaign is match-funded by the #iwill fund.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800759/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T12:01:24.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800759/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800759/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-04","Sports: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department is taking to increase the provision of organised sport for children outside schools.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","117380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800760","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-12","<p>No HM Treasury employees are paid through trusts rather than through PAYE.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800760/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T17:01:35.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800760/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800760/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-04","Treasury: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many and what proportion of Treasury employees are paid through trusts rather than through PAYE.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","117381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800761","Women and Equalities","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Department expects to start its review of the Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) during the first half of 2018 as part of the standard “tailored review” programme for public bodies. The EHRC’s resources, and its range of functions and responsibilities, will be among the issues which the review will cover.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800761/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:40:37.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800761/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800761/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-12-04","Equality and Human Rights Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, when she plans to begin her review of the Equality and Human Rights Commission; and whether the scope of that review will include staffing levels and the implications of recent redundancies.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","117382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800762","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-12","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>Small and medium-sized businesses in Witham can access support through GOV.UK and the Business Support Helpline. Government has also supported and invested in the creation of a network of 38 Growth Hubs (one in each Local Enterprise Partnership area), providing businesses across England with tailored advice and support. We, however, do not hold data at constituency level showing how many small and medium-sized businesses utilised this support.</p><p> </p><p>The South East Business Hub acts as the first port of call for businesses in the Witham constituency. Since its launch in 2014, the South East Business Hub has engaged and supported 7853 businesses and has helped 527 individuals looking to start up a new business in the East Sussex, Essex, Kent, Medway, Southend and Thurrock areas.</p><p> </p><p>As at end of June 2017, British Business Bank programmes have facilitated almost £18m to 119 businesses in the constituency of Witham*. This includes 36 Start-up Loans at a value of over £227,000.</p><p> </p><p>Through our Industrial Strategy, we will continue to back small and medium-sized business to grow and create jobs by providing an environment in which they can thrive.</p><p> </p><p><em>* This does not include the ENABLE Funding programme as we are unable to identify data at a constituency level.</em></p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800762/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T15:23:41.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800762/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800762/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Small Businesses: Witham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many small and medium-sized businesses in Witham constituency received support under each business support scheme operated by his Department since 2010.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","117383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800763","Department of Health","false","2017-12-12","<p>All, that is 100%, of permanently employed Departmental staff are paid via the Department or an arm’s length body’s payroll and are subject to PAYE.</p><p> </p><p>In respect of temporarily employed staff, all temporary staff are subject to a robust Departmental assurance process which ensures the appropriate tax is paid whether that be through the employing organisation in the case of secondments, the employing agency or the employing Professional services company in respect of contractors.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not collect information about the number of National Health Service staff paid through trusts rather than through PAYE. The mechanism for paying NHS staff is a matter for individual employers.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800763/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T15:47:38.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800763/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800763/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Department of Health: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many and what proportion of (a) Departmental employees and (b) NHS staff are paid through trusts rather than through PAYE.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","117384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800764","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-07","<p>The latest available data on Personal Independence Payment (PIP) and Disability Living Allowance (DLA) caseloads (i.e. claims in payment) broken down by year of age can be found at <a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Guidance on how to use Stat-Xplore can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/index.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/index.html</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Armed Forces Independence Payment (AFIP) is a weekly benefit which can be claimed by current or former members of the armed forces who were seriously injured whilst in the armed forces. There are currently no AFIP claimants under the age of 17.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800764/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T14:11:00.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800764/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800764/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-04","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many children aged less than 17 receive (a) disability living allowance, (b) personal independence payments and (c) armed forces independence payments.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","117385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800765","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-12","<p>No Cabinet Office employees are paid through trusts rather than through PAYE.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800765/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T15:52:32.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800765/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800765/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-04","Cabinet Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Cabinet Office, how many and what proportion of Cabinet Office employees are paid through trusts rather than through PAYE.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","117386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800766","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-07","<p>Warranties play an important role in providing protection for new home buyers. At present it is for warranty providers to determine the levels of protection which they provide through their warranties.</p><p>We are aware that existing mechanisms of redress in the housing sector can be confusing and disjointed. To address this we will in 2018 be examining options to improve redress for home buyers and will be consulting with consumers and the industry on introducing a single ombudsman.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800766/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:29:54.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800766/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800766/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-04","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the protection afforded to buyers by New Homes Warranties; if he will take steps to increase the level of protection afforded by those warranties; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","117387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800767","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The Department for Education does not pay any of its employees through trusts. The department does not hold information about the payment of staff employed in maintained schools.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800767/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T16:58:38.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800767/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800767/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Department for Education: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of (a) departmental employees and (b) maintained school staff are paid through trusts rather than through PAYE.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","117388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800768","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The information requested is not collected by the Department.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800768/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T17:09:22.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800768/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800768/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Schools: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education what data the Department collects on the number and proportion of staff employed by (a) academy and (b) free schools who are paid through trusts rather than through PAYE.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","117389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800769","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>NHS England has advised that under the terms of settlements agreed that parties are entitled to disclose only that an agreed resolution on the litigation has been reached and that these figures are confidential between the settling parties.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800769/answer",,,,,"117391","2017-12-07T15:05:01.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800769/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800769/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Clinical Commissioning Groups: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on how many occasions Care Commissioning Groups have paid a (a) financial settlement or (b) court award to an independent sector provider as a result of procurement and commissioning decisions, and if he will publish the Care Commissioning Groups and companies in each case.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","117390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800770","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>NHS England has advised that under the terms of settlements agreed that parties are entitled to disclose only that an agreed resolution on the litigation has been reached and that these figures are confidential between the settling parties.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800770/answer",,,,,"117390","2017-12-07T15:05:01.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800770/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800770/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Clinical Commissioning Groups: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the cost of litigation has been to Care Commissioning Groups regarding  procurement and commissioning decisions in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","117391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800771","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>The subject matter of the litigation was resolved by a settlement agreement reached at mediation. Under the terms of the settlement agreed the parties are entitled to disclose only that an agreed resolution on the litigation concerning the Surrey children’s procurement has been reached to a satisfactory conclusion for all parties with detailed terms confidential to the parties.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800771/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T14:39:38.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800771/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800771/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Virgin Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much has been paid by (a) each of the six Surrey Care Commissioning Groups, (b) Surrey County Council, and (c) NHS England, to Virgin Care as a result of litigation relating to the procurement of children’s services in Surrey.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","117392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800772","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-12","<p>We will publish a roadmap in 2018 that sets out how Government and industry will work together to reach the 2.4% target.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800772/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T15:17:23.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800772/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800772/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Research: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 67 of the Industrial Strategy, when he plans to publish a roadmap for meeting his target of increasing investment in R&D to 2.4 per cent of GDP by 2027.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800773","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>As part of the mediation and legal proceedings it was agreed that the operative terms of the settlement agreement which concluded the litigation concerning the Surrey children’s procurement be and remain confidential to the parties. It is very important, for reasons of public policy, that communications between parties to a mediation, and between those parties and the mediator, remain private and confidential.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800773/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T14:38:03.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800773/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800773/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Virgin Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the reasons were for not publishing the details of the settlement between Virgin Care and Surrey Care Commissioning Group relating to the procurement of children’s services in Surrey.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","117394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800774","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-12","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800774/answer","PQ117395.pdf","PQ117395.pdf","UKSA response","UKSA response",,"2017-12-12T16:00:41.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800774/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800774/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-04","Small Businesses: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many and what proportion of people in (a) Witham constituency and (b) the UK were employed by small and medium-sized enterprises in each year since 2007.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","117395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800775","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-11","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>UK Research and Innovation will work with the Government to develop a new competitive Strategic Priorities Fund. We are designing the operating model for the fund to ensure that we invest strategically whilst also giving certainty for the long term. Further details will be set out in due course.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800775/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-11T15:11:40.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800775/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800775/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Research: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 68 of Industrial Strategy: Building a Britain fit for the future, when he expects the new Strategic Priorities Fund to be operational.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800776","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-12","<p>As announced at Autumn Budget and in the Industrial Strategy, the government will introduce an Advanced Clearance Service for R&amp;D Expenditure Credit claims. The Advanced Clearance Service will be introduced following a pilot program with selected businesses. The pilot will start shortly.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800776/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T14:40:44.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800776/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800776/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-04","Research and Development Expenditure Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 69 of the Industrial Strategy, when he plans to introduce an advanced clearance service for R&D expenditure credit claims.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800777","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-12","<p>As announced at Autumn Budget and in the Industrial Strategy the government will work with small and medium sized businesses, and those developing new and emerging technologies, to ensure that they can access the maximum amount of support from R&amp;D tax credits, and will launch a campaign to raise awareness in these sectors. We will work with stakeholders and across government to develop and deliver this campaign by April 2018.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800777/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T14:41:30.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800777/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800777/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-04","Research and Development Expenditure Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to page 69 of Industrial Strategy: Building a Britain fit for the future, when the Government plans to launch the campaign to raise awareness of R&D tax credits.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800778","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-11","<p>I wrote to the Executive Chair (designate) of Research England on 24<sup>th</sup> November commissioning The Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) (and Research England from April 2018) to initiate work and consult with the sector on the development of a new Knowledge Exchange Framework (KEF), which will bring together a comparable range of measures of effective collaboration and knowledge exchange. This requests that a consultation on the Framework should be issued by Research England in Spring 2018, with the implementation of the KEF to take place in Autumn 2018. On 1 December, HEFCE published details of the Technical Group which will advise HEFCE/RE on the design and delivery of the new KEF metrics system, along with a call for evidence. Details are available at <a href="http://www.hefce.ac.uk/ke/kef/metrics/" target="_blank">http://www.hefce.ac.uk/ke/kef/metrics/</a>.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800778/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-11T15:09:58.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800778/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800778/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Universities: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 79 of the Industrial Strategy, what the timetable is for the establishment of the knowledge exchange framework.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800779","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The Adult Education Budget (AEB), introduced in 2016-17, replaced three separate funding lines: funding for adult vocational education outside of apprenticeships (previously held within the Adult Skills Budget), Community Learning and Discretionary Learner Support. We have maintained funding for the AEB in cash terms at £1.5 billion for this year to support adult skills participation. In the 2017-18 financial year, the overall funding for adult Further Education and skills (excluding capital) is £3.4 billion. This £3 billion will be available to directly support learning (this includes funding for offender learning which is now the responsibility of Ministry of Justice). This is set out in the Skills Funding Letter 2017-18 which can be viewed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/skills-funding-letter-april-2017-to-march-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/skills-funding-letter-april-2017-to-march-2018</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Furthermore, in the Spring 2017 Budget, the government announced the investment of an additional £500 million per year in England’s technical education system once T levels have been fully rolled out. We announced £20 million to help providers prepare for the delivery of T levels and to help teachers prepare for these changes.</p><p> </p><p>In the first wave of reforms to technical education, we are focussing on developing T levels as high quality level 3 technical study programmes for 16 to 19 year olds. We will consider how we adapt T levels so they are appropriate for adult learners and will review technical provision at levels 4 and 5. On 30 November we published a consultation setting out proposals for T levels and the wider reformed technical education system. It seeks views on how best to implement the reforms to make sure they are a success and meet the aims of the Sainsbury Report and the Post-16 Skills Plan.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800779/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T16:35:28.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800779/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800779/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Vocational Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to page 11 of the Industrial Strategy, what assessment she has made of the effect of funding cuts to the Adult Skills Budget since 2010 on the ability to establish a technical education system that rivals the best in the world.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800780","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Department has a robust, transparent accountability system in place for education providers which monitors the attainment, progress and destinations of those they teach, including those with special educational needs and disabilities (SEND). This system is based on performance data published through school and college performance tables and the inspection of schools and colleges through Ofsted. Ofsted inspections include consideration of how well schools and colleges meets the needs of pupils with SEND.</p><p>Multi-Academy Trust performance measures were published alongside school performance tables for the first time in 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Where schools and colleges are underperforming the Secretary of State has intervention powers set out in legislation and published in the Schools Causing Concern Guidance.</p><p> </p><p>Academies also operate under a robust system of financial oversight and accountability, founded on a clear framework, effective oversight and compliance based on proportionate risk assessment and intervention where required. Where concerns arise, the Education and Skills Funding Agency works with trusts to prevent financial instability and enable them to recover their financial position and return to stable governance. The sector remains in a strong position, with fewer than 2% of academy trusts subject to an active Financial Notice to Improve.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800780/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T12:07:03.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800780/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800780/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Schools: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to monitor the (a) educational attainment of, (b) financial performance of and (c) special educational needs support provided by education providers and multi-academy trusts.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","117401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800781","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-12","<p>The Government announced the new Strength in Places Fund in the Industrial Strategy White Paper. This new competitive funding stream will be delivered by UK Research and Innovation and will support areas to build on their science and innovation strengths and develop stronger local collaborative networks.</p><p>Exact details will be announced in due course, subject to the approval of a full business case; however the Government expects to launch a call for expressions of interest from local consortia in financial year 2018/19.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800781/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T16:12:52.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800781/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800781/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Science: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 85 of the Industrial Strategy, when he expects the Strength in Places Fund to be in operation.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800782","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>The department publishes statutory guidance for head teachers and governors on exclusion: ‘Exclusion from maintained schools, Academies and pupil referral units in England’. The guidance covers the process from start to finish, and includes specific requirements in relation to pupils with special educational needs and disability (SEND). In particular, the guidance sets out that, head teachers and governing bodies should make additional efforts to consider what extra support may be required to avoid exclusion of pupils with SEND, and as far as possible, should avoid permanently excluding pupils with an Education, Health and Care Plan or Statement.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800782/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T12:00:26.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800782/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800782/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Pupil Exclusions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what guidance her Department has issued to regulate the exclusion from school of  pupils with (a) special educational needs and (b) disabilities.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","117403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800783","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-11","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>A Memorandum of Understanding formalising the agreed Joint UK-China Science, Technology &amp; Innovation Strategy was signed by myself and my counterpart Vice Minister Wang Zhigang of the Chinese Ministry of Science &amp; Technology at a ceremony at the Royal Society on 6<sup>th</sup> December.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800783/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-11T15:04:08.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800783/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800783/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Science: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 85 of the Industrial Strategy, when he plans to agree the joint Science, Technology and Innovation Strategy with China.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","117404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800784","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-07","<p>The data available does not enable us to make an estimate of eligible disabled children to an acceptable level of precision.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested on the number of Tax-Free Childcare accounts for disabled children who have made a payment from the account is not available at the current time.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800784/answer",,,,,"117411","2017-12-07T14:24:25.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800784/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800784/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-04","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the answer of 1 December 2017, to Question 116033, for what reason the information on the number of disabled children eligible for Tax-Free Childcare is not available.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","117405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800785","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>NHS England allocated £650,000 to fund its Children and Young People’s Mental Health Commissioner Development Programme to deliver the ambitions set out in Future in Mind.</p><p> </p><p>The year-long learning programme will conclude in December 2017 and involves 115 commissioners enrolled from the health, public health, children’s services and youth justice system. The programme objectives are to develop commissioner skills, knowledge and confidence to deliver the whole system transformation described in Future in Mind. The tailored training includes co-production with service users and their families; partnership working across different sectors and routine use of data and outcome measurement.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800785/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T15:02:40.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800785/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800785/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much funding NHS England has allocated to the Children and young people’s mental health commissioning development programme, and what the objectives are of that programme.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","117406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800786","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>This information is not available in the format requested.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800786/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T14:52:59.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800786/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800786/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many and what proportion of children and young people’s services in England have a crisis intervention team.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","117407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800787","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>Data is collected by NHS Digital on the number of unplanned accident and emergency (A&amp;E) attendances for 0-17 years old within the A&amp;E patient group category of deliberate self-harm.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800787/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T15:00:45.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800787/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800787/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Self-harm: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 1 December 2017 to Question 116271, in what format is data collected on the number of children admitted to Accident and Emergency departments for self-harm.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","117408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800788","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>Future in Mind set out an ambitious agenda for whole system change which can only be achieved through a collaborative approach both locally and nationally across a range of settings including health, children’s services, and youth justice. The Children and Young People’s (CYP) Mental Health Improvement Team is a small team in NHS England that has embedded expertise in these areas. They provide leadership, advice and support such as sharing best-practice, learning and solutions to common challenges to a range of organisations and individuals including clinical networks, commissioners, providers and CYP Improving Access to Psychological Therapies collaboratives across the system to support delivery.</p><p> </p><p>It consists of 3.5 full time equivalent staff working in the central NHS England Children and Young People’s Mental Health Programme Team.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800788/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:18:05.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800788/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800788/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people work full-time in the children and young people's mental health improvement team.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","117409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800789","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-07","<p>This is an industry-led trial with the industry determining the terms and conditions on a commercial basis.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800789/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T13:27:34.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800789/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800789/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Railways: Concessions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reason the proposed railcard for ages 26 to 30 years will be available only for off-peak travel.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","117410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800790","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-07","<p>The data available does not enable us to make an estimate of eligible disabled children to an acceptable level of precision.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested on the number of Tax-Free Childcare accounts for disabled children who have made a payment from the account is not available at the current time.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800790/answer",,,,,"117405","2017-12-07T14:24:25.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800790/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800790/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-04","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 22 November 2017 to Question 115078, how many of the live tax-free childcare accounts for disabled children have had a payment made from the account.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","117411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800791","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-07","<p>The 26-30 railcard is being trialed by the rail industry on a commercial basis. While we will work with the industry to understand the findings and to learn from the trial, the findings of the trial will therefore be commercially sensitive. Given the commercial nature of this particular industry-led trial, it is not anticipated that there will be any cost to the public purse arising from the trial.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800791/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T12:55:43.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800791/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800791/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Railways: Concessions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse of the pilot scheme for the 26-30 rail card.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","117412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800792","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>We are still in the process of collating and categorising requests from local authorities for disapplication from the school finance regulations for the 2018-19 financial year. The information requested by the Rt hon. member for Kingston and Surbiton will not be available until approximately mid-December.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800792/answer",,,,,"117415","2017-12-07T17:18:58.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800792/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800792/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which local authorities have requested permission to disapply guidelines on the ring-fenced dedicated schools grant for the financial year 2018-19; and what is the disapplication each wishes to make.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","117413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800793","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>The gender diversity task and finish group includes practitioners, training providers, unions, academics and employers. As set out in the Early Years Workforce Strategy, the group will report to the department on the factors influencing the number of men in childcare and present possible solutions to increase this number.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800793/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:24:21.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800793/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800793/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Pre-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 4 December 2017 to Question 116575 on Pre-school Education: Recruitment, if he will publish the membership of the task and finish group.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","117414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800794","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>We are still in the process of collating and categorising requests from local authorities for disapplication from the school finance regulations for the 2018-19 financial year. The information requested by the Rt hon. member for Kingston and Surbiton will not be available until approximately mid-December.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800794/answer",,,,,"117413","2017-12-07T17:18:58.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800794/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800794/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which local authorities (a) submitted a request to disapply regulations (b) had a request to disapply regulations granted and (c) disapplied regulations relating to the ring-fenced dedicated schools grant in each of the last three financial years.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","117415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800795","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>Childminders, including grandparents who are childminders, cannot receive early years funding, including the new 30 hours’ entitlement, for related children. This is set out in Sections 18(4) and 20 of the Childcare Act 2006: <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2006/21/contents" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2006/21/contents</a>.</p><p>This long-standing position avoids creating an incentive for adults to register to become formal carers for related children they are already looking after on an informal basis.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800795/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:46:35.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800795/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800795/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Child Minding: Grandparents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the reasons are for grandparents who are childminders to be ineligible to receive 30-funded hours of childcare for their grandchildren.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","117416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800796","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-07","<p>DVSA management has engaged with representatives of the Public and Commercial Services (PCS) union throughout the development of the new driving test. DVSA management has considered all concerns raised by PCS.<strong><em> </em></strong></p><p> </p><p>The recent strike was not about the proposed changes to the test, but about a contract which PCS agreed, and which their members overwhelmingly supported in 2014. In adopting it, the members received a lump sum payment of up to £3,000 each.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800796/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T13:35:28.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800796/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800796/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions the management of DVSA management has had with the Public and Commercial Services union on that union's concerns relating to the new driving test.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","117417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800797","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-07","<p>DVSA does not require staff to declare membership of a recognised trades union. It is not therefore possible to identify whether members of the Public and Commercial Services Union working at DVSA have or have not been subject to disciplinary hearings or investigations.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800797/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T08:20:09.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800797/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800797/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many members of the Public and Commercial Services union working within DVSA have been subject to disciplinary hearings or investigations by management since 2015.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","117418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800798","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-07","<p>DVSA carried out a risk assessment of the new test in July 2017, and conducted further evaluations in September 2017. The report concluded that all elements of the driving test were low risk.</p><p> </p><p>DVSA also commissioned an independent report from Royal Society for the Prevention of Accidents to assess the risk of the changes to the test. This echoed the findings of the DVSA assessment that all aspects of the new elements of the driving test were low risk.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800798/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T14:34:56.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800798/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800798/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, who carried out the risk assessment on the new driving test; and what the findings of that assessment were.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","117419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800799","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-07","<p>HMP Hull will contact the Amy Johnson Arts Trust as part of the work that is underway to secure a permanent location for the full-scale replica of Amy Johnson’s Gipsy Moth.</p><p>A decision has not been reached on a permanent location since receiving notification the model had to move by February 2018.</p><p>HMP Hull continue to work with any interested parties to agree the most appropriate location for the model.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800799/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T16:27:55.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800799/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800799/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-04","Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department consulted the Amy Johnson Arts Trust before the decision was made on the permanent location of the replica of Amy Johnson's plane.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","117420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800800","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>The number of metered dose and dry powder inhalers prescribed in England in each of the last financial years can be found in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Time Period</p></td><td><p>Metered Dose Inhalers Total Number of Items</p></td><td><p>Metered Dose Inhalers Total Number of Inhalers</p></td><td><p>Dry Powder Inhalers Total Number of Items</p></td><td><p>Dry Powder Inhalers Total Number of Inhalers</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><sup>1</sup>Financial 2012/13</p></td><td><p>16,865,011</p></td><td><p>22,200,978</p></td><td><p>6,232,791</p></td><td><p>77,106,658</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial 2013/14</p></td><td><p>33,285,250</p></td><td><p>43,706,232</p></td><td><p>13,050,690</p></td><td><p>163,352,892</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial 2014/15</p></td><td><p>34,896,944</p></td><td><p>45,485,666</p></td><td><p>13,796,383</p></td><td><p>170,303,819</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial 2015/16</p></td><td><p>34,999,252</p></td><td><p>45,253,625</p></td><td><p>14,120,657</p></td><td><p>169,800,742</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial 2016/17</p></td><td><p>35,821,122</p></td><td><p>45,780,844</p></td><td><p>14,456,394</p></td><td><p>168,747,335</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><sup>2</sup>Financial 2017/18</p></td><td><p>17,456,205</p></td><td><p>22,171,264</p></td><td><p>7,181,685</p></td><td><p>83,215,366</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>173,323,784</p></td><td><p>224,598,609</p></td><td><p>68,838,600</p></td><td><p>832,526,812</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p><sup>1</sup>Financial 2012/13 covers time period October 2012 to March 2013</p><p> </p><p><sup>2</sup>Financial 2017/18 covers time period April 2017 to September 2017</p><p> </p><p>This information has been provided by the NHS Business Services Authority.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800800/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:50:30.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800800/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800800/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Lung Diseases: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) metered-dose and (b) dry powder inhalers were prescribed in England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","117421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800801","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Department has not undertaken a cost-benefit analysis. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has made assessments on the health effectiveness of inhalers, which are used to treat a number of health conditions and have published a number of resources to assist clinicians in treating those conditions. The Department is not leading on policies related to fluorinated greenhouse gases. We, however, will continue to provide advice to Department for Environment Food and Rural Affairs on any potential health impact in relation to their policies.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800801/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:46:50.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800801/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800801/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Lung Diseases: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department has undertaken a cost-benefit analysis of encouraging the prescription of more dry powder inhalers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","117422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800802","Department of Health","false","2017-12-13","<p>In order to further support the National Health Service and local communities, the Government provided £2 million to make public access defibrillators more widely available and to increase the numbers of people trained in cardiopulmonary resuscitation.</p><p> </p><p>Local commissioners, working closely with their communities, are best placed to make decisions on the location of defibrillators.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800802/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-13T14:08:46.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800802/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800802/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to co-ordinate the location of defibrillators to ensure that those areas that do not have access to a defibrillator can access one.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800803","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-12","<p>Former presidents Lula da Silva and Dilma Rouseff are subject to a judicial process as part of a major anti-corruption investigation. We understand that due process is being followed. We have not made any representations on this issue.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800803/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T13:51:06.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800803/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800803/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-04","Brazil: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Government of Brazil to ensure that the human rights of former Presidents Lula and Rousseff are upheld.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800804","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-07","<p>Whilst we recommend that cat owners have their cats microchipped, there are no plans to make this compulsory. Microchipping was made compulsory for dogs not just to help reunite stray dogs with their owners, but also because stray dogs can generate public safety and environmental issues.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800804/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T19:08:00.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800804/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800804/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-04","Cats: Tagging","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will introduce compulsory microchipping of domestic cats.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800805","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-11","<p>The Department has no plans at present to bring forward proposals to amend legislation ON reporting animal deaths on the road. However, the police do advise drivers that, if possible, they should make enquiries to ascertain the owner of domestic animals such as cats, and inform them of the situation. In addition, Rule 286 of The Highway Code also advises drivers to report any accident involving an animal to the police.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800805/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-11T15:01:02.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800805/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800805/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward proposals to amend animal welfare legislation to give greater protection to cats injured or killed in road traffic accidents.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800806","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-12","<p>With the enactment of the Cities and Local Government Devolution Act 2016, the procedures for two tier local authorities wishing to reorganise themselves are for one or more of the councils concerned to submit a proposal for a reorganised structure to the Secretary of State who must consider it.</p><p>As I told the House on 28 February 2017 (PQ 65271) the criteria for assessing such proposals is whether the proposal, if implemented, is likely to improve the area's local government, commands a good deal of local support in the area, and whether the area itself is a credible geography for the proposed new structure. Having considered such a proposal, the Secretary of State will announce whether or not he is minded, subject to Parliamentary approval, to implement it.</p><p>After a period during which those interested may make representations to the Secretary of State, he will then take his final decision and invite Parliament to approve the secondary legislation necessary to implement the proposal where this is his decision.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800806/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T17:17:00.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800806/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800806/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-04","Local Government: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what procedures are in place for those current two-tier local authority areas which wish to reorganise themselves.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800807","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Government’s priority is to maintain affordable, clean and secure energy supplies for businesses and households. As part of this we share the EU’s ambition to make energy trading easier and more efficient by opening up national markets and increasing the level of interconnection between them.</p><p>We want to continue arrangements which allow the efficient trade in electricity and gas, both on the island of Ireland and between the UK and continental Europe, and to continue to closely collaborate on current and future regulatory and technical arrangements.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800807/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T16:57:06.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800807/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800807/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","EU Energy Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether it is the Government's policy to remain in the EU internal energy market after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","117428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800808","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-11","<p>The European Union (Withdrawal Bill) will convert existing EU chemicals law, including REACH, into domestic law wherever practical, giving consumers and businesses as much certainty as possible. The UK is strongly committed to the effective and safe management of chemicals. That will not change when we leave the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The Government published its position paper on continuity in the availability of goods for the EU and the UK in August. This paper set out the principles the UK is proposing for ensuring the availability of goods after Exit. This includes seeking to avoid unnecessary duplication of compliance activity for businesses and proposing that the UK and EU markets continue to recognise the validity of registrations issued prior to exit.</p><p> </p><p>While it would not be appropriate to pre-judge the outcome of the negotiations we will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue cooperation in chemicals regulation in the best interests of both the UK and the EU.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800808/answer",,,,,"117430","2017-12-11T17:22:41.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800808/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800808/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-04","Chemicals: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether it is the Government's policy to remain part of the REACH system for authorising chemicals after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","117429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800809","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-11","<p>The European Union (Withdrawal Bill) will convert existing EU chemicals law, including REACH, into domestic law wherever practical, giving consumers and businesses as much certainty as possible. The UK is strongly committed to the effective and safe management of chemicals. That will not change when we leave the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The Government published its position paper on continuity in the availability of goods for the EU and the UK in August. This paper set out the principles the UK is proposing for ensuring the availability of goods after Exit. This includes seeking to avoid unnecessary duplication of compliance activity for businesses and proposing that the UK and EU markets continue to recognise the validity of registrations issued prior to exit.</p><p> </p><p>While it would not be appropriate to pre-judge the outcome of the negotiations we will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue cooperation in chemicals regulation in the best interests of both the UK and the EU.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800809/answer",,,,,"117429","2017-12-11T17:22:41.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800809/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800809/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-04","Chemicals: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether UK registrations under the EU Registration, Evaluation, Authorisation & Restriction of Chemicals regulation will continue to be recognised after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","117430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800810","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>The funding for construction skills was announced in the Budget, as part of the National Retraining Scheme. Most of the funding will be a construction skills fund for England, which will support the government’s ambition to build many more new homes during this parliament.</p><p> </p><p>The department will publish criteria for the fund early next year. The fund will help to build construction training facilities attached to housing developments, and will support adult students to retrain as construction workers. We will welcome bids from colleges and developers from across the country.</p><p> </p><p>There will also be £5 million for construction skills in the West Midlands, as part of the second devolution deal.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800810/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T16:52:08.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800810/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800810/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Construction: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to page 119 of the Government's Industrial Strategy, if she will publish the programmes to be funded through the £34 million investment in innovative construction training programmes in the (a) Liverpool City Region and (b) UK.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","117431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800811","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-07","<p>I refer my Hon Friend to the answer given by my Hon Friend, the Minister for Local Government, on 28 February 2017, to Question UIN 65271.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800811/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:36:46.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800811/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800811/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-04","Local Government: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Written Statement of 7 November 2017, HCWS 232, on local government improvement, what criteria the Government has set by which it will decide whether the necessary local consent has been secured; if he will publish those criteria; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","117432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800812","Department of Health","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Government is working with the Association of British Insurers to renew the existing Concordat and Moratorium. We will be seeking the views of an established group of stakeholders with a view to publication in early 2018 ahead of the end date of the Concordat and Moratorium in November 2019.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800812/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:16:56.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800812/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800812/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-04","Genetics: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if the Government will consult on extending the moratorium that allows people not to declare the results of genetic tests to insurers after 1 November 2019; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","117433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800813","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Department regularly engages with the Welsh Government to ensure a coordinated, joined up approach to investment in the strategic road network. The Department is in consultation with the ports and logistics industry, in order to help ensure that movement through ports and across borders is as frictionless as possible, whatever the outcome of negotiations on future arrangements for trade with the EU.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800813/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T08:34:05.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800813/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800813/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Roads: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with the Welsh Government on upgrades or improvements to the (a) A55 and (b) M4/A40 corridor to cope with potential delays to freight traffic a result of additional customs procedures in the event of the UK leaving the EU customs union.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","117434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800814","Home Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>Border Force does not lead on the purchase of land and / or facilities at ports to carry customs checks. It is the responsibility of Port Operators to provide suitable facilities as laid out in Customs legislation.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800814/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T12:48:15.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800814/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800814/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-04","Ports: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what additional purchases of (a) land and (b) facilities her Department has made at each of the Welsh ports to establish additional customs facilities in the 12 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","117435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800815","Home Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>This Government has ensured that sufficient resources are available to ensure the security of the border is not compromised. Security of the border cannot be measured by numbers of staff.</p><p>Border Force uses a sophisticated combination of experienced officers, intelligence, data, technology and partnership working. Border Force resources in Wales are reviewed on a regular basis as part of the wider Border Force business planning process which is led by the Director General of Border Force.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800815/answer",,,,,"117437","2017-12-07T12:48:02.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800815/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800815/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-04","UK Border Force: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Border Force staff are deployed in Wales by location; and how many of those staff are trained in customs operations.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","117436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800816","Home Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>This Government has ensured that sufficient resources are available to ensure the security of the border is not compromised. Security of the border cannot be measured by numbers of staff.</p><p>Border Force uses a sophisticated combination of experienced officers, intelligence, data, technology and partnership working. Border Force resources in Wales are reviewed on a regular basis as part of the wider Border Force business planning process which is led by the Director General of Border Force.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800816/answer",,,,,"117436","2017-12-07T12:48:02.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800816/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800816/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-04","UK Border Force: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of the recent additional Border Force officers she has recruited will be (a) deployed to Wales and (b) replacing vacant positions.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","117437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800817","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>​The Ambassador has remained in contact with senior members of the General People's Congress (GPC). Discussion has focused on the breakdown of the alliance between the Houthis and the GPC. The Foreign Secretary has publicly called for restraint.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800817/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T17:36:12.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800817/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800817/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-04","Yemen: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions the UK Ambassador to Yemen has had with the officials of the former President Saleh of Yemen since the President's death on 4 December 2017.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","117438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800818","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Industrial Strategy White Paper has set out a range of measures aimed at increasing investment from the private and public sector, which will both be vital in meeting the objective of increasing our productivity and earning power for people across the UK. This includes a commitment to increase total R&amp;D investment to 2.4% of GDP by 2027.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800818/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T16:16:22.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800818/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800818/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Industry: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment the Government has made of the level of private sector investment required to deliver on the objectives of the Industrial Strategy.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","117439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800819","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>From April 2018, we plan to allow levy-paying employers to transfer up to 10% of the annual value of their funds to other employers, including to smaller employers in their supply chain through the apprenticeship service. The 10% refers to the maximum amount of funds a levy-paying employer can transfer. State aid rules apply to transferred funds which mean that the maximum amount that an organisation can receive is €2 million over 3 years.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800819/answer",,,,,"117118","2017-12-07T16:55:55.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800819/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800819/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Apprentices: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the 10 percent annual value  that a company can transfer to another company from its apprenticeship service account is the total amount that can be transferred, or the total amount another company can receive.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","117440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800820","Home Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>If a child under the age of 18 meets the requirements of the Withdrawal Agreement in their own right they can apply for settled status independently of their parents. However, we would expect most children under the age of 18 to apply as the family member of their EU citizen parent.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800820/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T12:48:23.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800820/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800820/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-04","Immigration: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether children of parents with EU citizenship will be able to apply for settled status in their own right before they reach the age of 18.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","117441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800821","Home Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>Police Information Notices (PINs) are an operational tool used by some police forces in England and Wales. Their use is the responsibility of the police and the issuing of guidance about them is the responsibility of the College of Policing. Information on their use is not collected centrally. The issuance of Police Information Notices (PINs) is an operational matter for police forces. Responsibility for the publication of information relating to PINs rests with Chief Constables.</p><p> </p><p>Following this year’s joint inspection by Her Majesty’s Inspectorate of Constabulary and Fire &amp; Rescue Service and Her Majesty’s Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) Inspectorate which recommended the police cease use of PINs, we have been working with the National Policing Lead and the College of Policing on next steps on the use of PINs. The Home Secretary also chaired a National Oversight Group to ensure the inspection’s findings are acted upon.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800821/answer",,,,,"117443 ; 117444","2017-12-07T12:47:38.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800821/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800821/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-04","Police: Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which constabularies have stopped using using Police Information Notices.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","117442"
