"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798647","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-06","<p>The UK enjoys a lasting, deep and broad partnership with India. The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip, spoke to Indian External Affairs Minister Sushma Swaraj on 22 November about the forthcoming Commonwealth Summit and consular issues. He congratulated India on its re-election to the International Court of Justice. My noble friend the Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon, met amongst others, Prime Minister Modi, External Affairs Minister Swaraj and Minister of State for External Affairs MJ Akbar during his visit to Delhi on 23-24 November and reinforced our valuable cooperation on cyber security. I spoke to Minister of State for External Affairs M J Akbar on 29 November to welcome the acquittal of the six British nationals imprisoned in Chennai and other current consular issues.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798647/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-06T16:11:28.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798647/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798647/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-01","India: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last met his counterpart in India; and what issues were discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","117041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798648","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-12","<p>We do not hold this information.</p><p> </p><p>Energy suppliers have their own individual systems and criteria for recording offers for installations of a smart meter.</p><p> </p><p>The rollout of smart meters is on track to deliver significant benefits, including putting an end to estimated bills, and is set to save consumers £300m in 2020 alone.</p><p> </p><p>Suppliers are mandated by government to offer every household and small business a smart meter by 2020, and remain committed to this target.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798648/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T11:57:58.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798648/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798648/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-01","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many homes will have been offered a smart meter in the West Midlands by the end of 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","117042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798649","Department of Health","false","2017-12-06","<p>Acid sphingomyelinase deficiency is a lysosomal storage disorder (LSD). NHS England and its predecessor organisation have commissioned a national service for patients with LSDs since April 2005. The service is commissioned from eight expert centres and NHS England monitors these expert centres against the agreed service specification:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/e06-lyso-stor-dis-child.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/e06-lyso-stor-dis-child.pdf</a></p><p>The active caseload of LSD patients treated in the service is just under 2,000. NHS England’s Highly Specialised Commissioning team conducts an annual clinical audit meeting with the multidisciplinary teams from all the providers and with representatives from relevant patient groups.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798649/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-06T12:32:27.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798649/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798649/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-01","Hereditary Diseases: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of treatment provision for people diagnosed with Acid Sphingomyelinase Deficiency.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","117043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798650","Department of Health","false","2017-12-06","<p>NHS England and its predecessor have commissioned the Alström Syndrome Service (for all ages) since April 2009 at two centres including the Birmingham Women and Children’s Hospital (for paediatric service) and the University Hospitals of Birmingham (for the adult service). These two centres work together, including on transition planning and work in line with the Alström service specification.</p><p> </p><p>There are currently 74 patients on the caseload. NHS England’s Highly Specialised Commissioning team conducts an annual clinical audit meeting with the multidisciplinary team from both providers and the patient group Alström Syndrome UK, the last was held in March 2017.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798650/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-06T12:33:55.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798650/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798650/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-01","Hereditary Diseases: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of treatment provision for people diagnosed with Alström syndrome.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","117044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798651","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Board of the Student Loans Company (SLC) currently has three male and three female non-executive members. Following an open recruitment earlier this year, two further non-executive members, one male and one female, are shortly due to be appointed to the SLC Board.</p><p> </p><p>I will continue to monitor diversity on the SLC Board to ensure that it has an appropriate and diverse range of skills and backgrounds.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798651/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T16:08:44.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798651/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798651/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798651/answer/previousversion/27730","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","60","Education","Education","2017-12-01","Student Loans Company","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to (a) increase the membership and (b) expand the diversity of the Board of the Student Loans Company.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","117045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798652","Department of Health","false","2017-12-08","<p>The data is not held centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798652/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-08T10:59:51.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798652/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798652/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-01","Ambulance Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many fatalities have occurred when patients were (a) waiting for an ambulance to arrive and (b) in transit to a health facility, broken down by Ambulance Trust, for each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798653","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Government’s policy is to introduce a ban on the use of wild animals in travelling circuses as soon as Parliamentary time allows. In the interim, the welfare of any wild animals still being used by travelling circuses in England is protected by the Welfare of Wild Animals in Travelling Circuses (England) Regulations 2012.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798653/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T18:55:46.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798653/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798653/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-01","Circuses: Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether he plans to introduce legislative proposals to ban the use of animals in travelling circuses in the current session of Parliament.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798654","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-12","<p>We are working closely with the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on our response to the Call for Evidence on the remit of the Groceries Code Adjudicator. This will be published in due course.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798654/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-12T11:58:33.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798654/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798654/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-01","Groceries Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when his Department expects to publish its response to its consultation on extending the remit of the Groceries Code Adjudicator which closed in January 2017.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798655","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-07","<p>No specific assessment of these issues has been made. It is too early to say exactly what would be covered in a future deal with the United States. Leaving the EU is a golden opportunity for us to secure bold and ambitious trade agreements that work for consumers, farmers, and businesses in the UK. We will not water down our standards as part of any future trade deals.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798655/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T18:45:33.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798655/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798655/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-01","Food: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on (a) food standards and (b) salmonella rates in eggs of a free trade agreement with the United States.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","117049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798656","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-11","<p>The internal FCO review into our position towards the Safe Schools Declaration recently concluded. The Government is considering its implications and assessing next steps.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798656/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-11T16:06:48.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798656/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798656/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-01","Armed Conflict: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he expects to conclude his review on whether the UK Government should sign the Safe Schools Declaration.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","117050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798657","Home Office","false","2017-12-06","<p>On 26 November, the Home Secretary [I] announced an in-depth assessment of protests outside abortion clinics, following reports that some women have been subjected to harassment and intimidating behaviour from protestors when visiting family planning clinics to seek information, advice and services from medical professionals.</p><p> </p><p>Undertaken by Home Office officials, the review will collect detailed evidence to inform recommendations on what more needs to be done to ensure that the police, healthcare providers and local authorities have the right powers to protect women making these tough decisions.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office does not hold the information requested on how many individuals were prosecuted and convicted for alleged harassment or intimidation outside abortion facilities. Information on the number of prosecutions or convictions is the responsibility of the Ministry of Justice and they have informed us that they do not hold the requested information.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798657/answer",,,,,"117052 ; 117054","2017-12-06T13:17:05.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798657/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/798657/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-01","Abortion: Clinics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for her Department’s Review into harassment outside abortion facilities; what funding she has allocated to that review; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","117051"
