"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797859","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-05","<p>The guidance and application information for the European Capital of Culture 2023 competition were both produced by the European Commission so there was no cost to the UK Government.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797859/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T11:07:42.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797859/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797859/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-11-30","European Capital of Culture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate she has made of the total (a) cost and (b) man-hours relating to her Department on the preparation of guidance and application information for cities wishing to become European Capital of Culture 2023.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","116766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797860","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-07","<p>A summary of the budget profiles up to 2020/21 will be published as part of my Department’s main estimates for 2018/19.</p><p>The Autumn Budget demonstrated our determination to fix the broken housing market, allocating funding as far ahead as 2022-23. This includes £15 billion of new financial support over the next five years, bringing the total package of financial support to £44 billion over the period.</p><p>New financial support measures announced at Autumn Budget for the four years to 2020-21 are set in the Budget book.</p><p>On the new financial guarantees for house building outlined at Autumn Budget, we will be working to engage the market over coming months as to the most effective way of deploying these guarantees in order to pursue our housing goals.</p><p>Following the additional financial support for housing announced in the Autumn Budget, my Department is now reviewing the budget profiles of existing housing programmes to ensure these are aligned with this new funding.</p><p>We will discuss appropriate arrangements and funding for London with the Mayor and the Greater London Authority.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797860/answer",,,,,"116758 ; 116762 ; 116764 ; 116765 ; 116777 ; 116778 ; 116781 ; 116783","2017-12-07T17:55:25.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797860/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797860/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-30","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of total spending on small sites infrastructure and remediation, excluding Barnett consequential spending, in (a) the Greater London Authority area (b) England in each of the next four financial years to 2020-21.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","116767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797861","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-05","<p>The UK will continue to be legally bound by the Paris Agreement after it leaves the EU; this is because it is Party to the Agreement both in its own right and through the EU.</p><p>Climate change is one of the most serious issues that we are facing and we remain firmly committed to the Paris Agreement and our emissions reduction and climate finance efforts, which are the result of this commitment. Climate change can only be tackled by nations working together and we will continue to work closely with the EU on this issue.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797861/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T16:26:08.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797861/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797861/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-30","Climate Change Convention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his Department's policy is on the UK continuing to be legally bound by the Paris Agreement after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","116768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797862","Department for Education","false","2017-12-05","<p>The accompanying table provides information on permanent and fixed-period exclusions of pupils with Education, Health and Care plans and Statements of Special Educational Needs in each local council in the West Midlands in each of the last five years.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797862/answer","116769 - Attach.xlsx","116769 - Attach.xlsx","116769 Accompanying Table","116769 Accompanying Table",,"2017-12-05T17:13:22.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797862/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797862/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-30","Special Educational Needs: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children with an (a) Education, Health and Care Plan and (b) Statement of Educational Needs and Disability received a permanent or fixed-term exclusion in each local authority in the West Midlands in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","116769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797863","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-06","<p>All government departments, agencies and arm’s-length bodies (ALBs) use <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a>. Parts of their portfolio may have an exemption, but they all have a presence on <a href="http://gov.uk" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a>.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797863/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-06T15:05:44.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797863/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797863/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-30","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many Government departments, agencies and arms’ length bodies do not use the gov.uk website.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","116770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797864","Department for Education","false","2017-12-05","<p>The number of children and young people with an education, health and care plan in 2017 for England, by region and by local council, is available in table 3 on the department’s website at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statements-of-sen-and-ehc-plans-england-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statements-of-sen-and-ehc-plans-england-2017</a>.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797864/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T17:30:43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797864/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797864/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-30","Special Educational Needs: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many education, health and care plans have been provided to children in (a) the West Midlands (b) Coventry in 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","116771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797865","Department for Education","false","2017-12-05","<p>The number of children and young people assessed and a decision taken whether or not to issue an education, health and care plan for England, by region and by local council, are available on the department’s website.</p><p>The latest data available are for the 2016 calendar year.</p><p>For the 2016 calendar year, this information is available in table 7 on the department’s website at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statements-of-sen-and-ehc-plans-england-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statements-of-sen-and-ehc-plans-england-2017</a>.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797865/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T17:29:18.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797865/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797865/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-30","Special Educational Needs: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many applications have been made for education, health and care plans in (a) the West Midlands, (b) Coventry in 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","116772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797866","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-06","<p>The allocation of bonuses from the Trustees’ share of surpluses in the Mineworkers’ Pension Scheme is a matter for the Trustees.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797866/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-06T16:23:44.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797866/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797866/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-30","Mineworkers' Pension Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to ensure that mineworkers in deprived areas have access to a proportionate share of the profits made by the Mineworkers' Pension Scheme.","false","Biography information for Ben Bradley","Mansfield","Ben Bradley","116773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797867","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>42 new websites were approved through the Governments spending controls process between 5th April 2013 - 19th July 2017.</p><p> </p><p>14 new sub-websites (as part of existing website) were approved between 31st July 2013 - 14th August 2017.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797867/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T11:15:24.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797867/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797867/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-30","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many new Government websites have been approved through the Government's spending controls process in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","116774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797868","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>The number of applications received by the Naming and Approvals Committee from 30 October 2012 - 1 November 2017 is 918. Of these, 663 were approved.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797868/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T11:16:13.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797868/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797868/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-30","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many applications have been (a) received and (b) approved by the Naming and Approvals Committee in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","116775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797869","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-06","<p>The fly-tipping statistics for England show there were 1,571 successful prosecutions for fly-tipping by local authorities in 2016/17. The table below shows how many vehicles involved in fly-tipping have been seized by local authorities in the past five years.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Vehicles seized</strong></p></td><td><p>45</p></td><td><p>85</p></td><td><p>71</p></td><td><p>129</p></td><td><p>197</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797869/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-06T15:44:14.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797869/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797869/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-11-30","Fly-tipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many successful convictions there have been for fly tipping in the past 12 months; and how many vehicles used in fly tipping have been seized and crushed in the past five years.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","116776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797870","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-07","<p>A summary of the budget profiles up to 2020/21 will be published as part of my Department’s main estimates for 2018/19.</p><p>The Autumn Budget demonstrated our determination to fix the broken housing market, allocating funding as far ahead as 2022-23. This includes £15 billion of new financial support over the next five years, bringing the total package of financial support to £44 billion over the period.</p><p>New financial support measures announced at Autumn Budget for the four years to 2020-21 are set in the Budget book.</p><p>On the new financial guarantees for house building outlined at Autumn Budget, we will be working to engage the market over coming months as to the most effective way of deploying these guarantees in order to pursue our housing goals.</p><p>Following the additional financial support for housing announced in the Autumn Budget, my Department is now reviewing the budget profiles of existing housing programmes to ensure these are aligned with this new funding.</p><p>We will discuss appropriate arrangements and funding for London with the Mayor and the Greater London Authority.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797870/answer",,,,,"116758 ; 116762 ; 116764 ; 116765 ; 116767 ; 116778 ; 116781 ; 116783","2017-12-07T17:55:25.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797870/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797870/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-30","Housing Estates: Regeneration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much funding has been allocated for estate regeneration in (a) the Greater London Authority area and (b) England in each of the next four financial years to 2020/21; and of how much of that funding is (i) grant spending and (ii) loans.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","116777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797871","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-07","<p>A summary of the budget profiles up to 2020/21 will be published as part of my Department’s main estimates for 2018/19.</p><p>The Autumn Budget demonstrated our determination to fix the broken housing market, allocating funding as far ahead as 2022-23. This includes £15 billion of new financial support over the next five years, bringing the total package of financial support to £44 billion over the period.</p><p>New financial support measures announced at Autumn Budget for the four years to 2020-21 are set in the Budget book.</p><p>On the new financial guarantees for house building outlined at Autumn Budget, we will be working to engage the market over coming months as to the most effective way of deploying these guarantees in order to pursue our housing goals.</p><p>Following the additional financial support for housing announced in the Autumn Budget, my Department is now reviewing the budget profiles of existing housing programmes to ensure these are aligned with this new funding.</p><p>We will discuss appropriate arrangements and funding for London with the Mayor and the Greater London Authority.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797871/answer",,,,,"116758 ; 116762 ; 116764 ; 116765 ; 116767 ; 116777 ; 116781 ; 116783","2017-12-07T17:55:25.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797871/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797871/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-30","Garden Communities: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of total spending on garden cities, towns and villages, excluding Barnett consequential spending, in (a) the Greater London Authority area and (b) England in each of  the next four financial years to 2020-21.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","116778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797872","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-08","<p>The Government has not made a formal assessment of the regulation of cryptocurrencies in other countries, though it is aware that industry has done so (for example https://bravenewcoin.com/news/icos-and-cryptocurrencies-a-rough-guide-to-global-regulation/) and, as with all policy, continues to monitor developments.</p><p>The Government is currently negotiating amendments to the 4th Anti-Money Laundering Directive that we expect to bring virtual currency exchange platforms and custodian wallet providers into the scope of Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorist Financing regulation. This will require such firms to conduct due diligence upon their customers, with their activities being overseen by national competent authorities for these areas. The government supports the intention behind these amendments. We expect these negotiations to conclude at EU level in late 2017/early 2018.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797872/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-08T08:25:56.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797872/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797872/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-30","Cryptocurrencies: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of international efforts to regulate crypto-currencies; and whether his Department has any plans to regulate crypto-currencies in the UK.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","116779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797873","Home Office","false","2017-12-05","<p>Tacking modern slavery and human trafficking is a high priority for HMG and we will continue to work closely with EU partners on this issue. The details of the UK’s future relationship with the EU will be subject to negotiation. Public safety in the UK and the rest of Europe will be at the heart of our negotiations.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797873/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T14:08:38.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797873/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797873/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-30","Human Trafficking: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of the UK leaving the EU on human trafficking in Wales.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","116780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797874","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-07","<p>A summary of the budget profiles up to 2020/21 will be published as part of my Department’s main estimates for 2018/19.</p><p>The Autumn Budget demonstrated our determination to fix the broken housing market, allocating funding as far ahead as 2022-23. This includes £15 billion of new financial support over the next five years, bringing the total package of financial support to £44 billion over the period.</p><p>New financial support measures announced at Autumn Budget for the four years to 2020-21 are set in the Budget book.</p><p>On the new financial guarantees for house building outlined at Autumn Budget, we will be working to engage the market over coming months as to the most effective way of deploying these guarantees in order to pursue our housing goals.</p><p>Following the additional financial support for housing announced in the Autumn Budget, my Department is now reviewing the budget profiles of existing housing programmes to ensure these are aligned with this new funding.</p><p>We will discuss appropriate arrangements and funding for London with the Mayor and the Greater London Authority.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797874/answer",,,,,"116758 ; 116762 ; 116764 ; 116765 ; 116767 ; 116777 ; 116778 ; 116783","2017-12-07T17:55:25.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797874/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797874/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-30","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of total spending on the Home Building Fund, excluding Barnett consequential spending, in (a) the Greater London Authority area and (b) England in each of the next four financial years