e that these data have been extracted from large administrative data systems generated by the courts and police forces. As a consequence, care should be taken to ensure data collection processes and their inevitable limitations are taken into account when those data are used.</p><p> </p><p>We are committed to doing all we can to address the issues around female offending so we can better protect the public and deliver more effective rehabilitation. We also are developing a strategy for female offenders, in England and Wales, to improve outcomes for women in the community and custody.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797925/answer",,,,,"116829","2017-12-08T12:36:24.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797925/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797925/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-30","Prison Sentences: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the average number of Welsh women sentenced to prison per month is.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","116832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797926","Department of Health","false","2017-12-05","<p>The Life Sciences Industrial Strategy (LSIS) set out the ambition to make the United Kingdom a global hub for clinical research and medical innovation. The Government welcomed the ambition of the LSIS, and is working in partnership with industry to deliver this through the upcoming Sector Deal.</p><p> </p><p>Our commitment to making a reality of the Accelerated Access Review was also set out in our publication on 3 November. Here, we committed to improving collaboration between the National Health Service and industry, and to improve the access and uptake of innovative medicines and treatments, including the ambition to accelerate patient access by up to four years.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797926/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T16:54:04.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797926/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797926/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-30","Drugs: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to encourage greater collaboration between investment in life sciences and innovative medicines in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","116833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797927","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-08","<p>The Control’s current forecast period is set to 2025. Potential new nuclear projects, after Hinkley Point C, are expected to become fully operational beyond 2025 and are therefore not affected by the commitment to no new levies up until this date.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will keep both the forecast period and Control under regular review. This will include considering how the Control could work after 2025.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797927/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-08T14:42:17.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797927/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797927/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-30","Nuclear Power: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether proposals for Contracts for Difference for new nuclear power stations other than Hinkley Point C will count as new levies under the Control for New Carbon Levies.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","116834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797928","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-05","<p>HMP Hull created a full-scale replica of Amy Johnson’s Gipsy Moth as part of the Hull City of Culture 2017 programme and the prison’s reducing reoffending initiative.</p><p> </p><p>HMP Hull approached and held discussions about the permanent placement of the replica Gipsy Moth with the City of Culture organisation, Network Rail for the use of Paragon Station, Curator Hull Museums, Museums Registrar (East Riding) and Sewerby Hall before the decision was taken to locate house the replica at Yorkshire Air Museum.</p><p> </p><p>The City of Culture organisation have since been approached by St Stephen’s shopping centre to express an interest in housing the replica model, this is currently being considered.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797928/answer",,,,,"116830","2017-12-05T15:24:20.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797928/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797928/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-30","Aircraft: Kingston upon Hull","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will take steps to ensure that the replica of Amy Johnson's Tiger Moth produced in HMP Hull remains in Hull.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","116835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797929","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-06","<p>In the Clean Growth Strategy the Government committed to extend support for home energy efficiency improvements until 2028 at least at the current level of Energy Company Obligation (ECO) funding. We will review the best form of support beyond 2022, including how it should be funded.</p><p> </p><p>We have committed to extend ECO at £640m per annum until 2022 and will be consulting on the next phase of the scheme (2018 – 2022) early next year.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797929/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-06T16:24:34.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797929/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797929/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-30","Energy Companies Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his review of support for the Energy Company Obligation beyond 2022 as set out in the Clean Growth Strategy of October 2017 will be based on the introduction of new levies to support the scheme.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","116836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797930","Department for Education","false","2017-12-08","<p>The Department is committed to ensuring schools are able to employ good quality supply teachers at value for money when needed. Local Authority supply pools are one of many approaches to providing supply teachers.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797930/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-08T14:03:49.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797930/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797930/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-30","Supply Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether he has made an assessment of the potential merits of reintroducing the Local Educational Authority supply pool for schools in England.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","116837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797931","Department of Health","false","2017-12-05","<p>The most important attraction for companies considering investing in research in the United Kingdom is the availability of world-class scientific expertise, which is the focus of the Government’s effort to ensure the UK remains at the forefront of global research and development. There is no obvious reason why National Health Service spend on pharmaceuticals should significantly affect decisions to invest in research and development in the UK. NHS spending on pharmaceuticals has risen by 41% between 2007/08 and 2016/17.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797931/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T16:43:53.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797931/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797931/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-30","Drugs: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of decreasing NHS spending on pharmaceuticals on the attractiveness of the UK as a location for research and development.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","116838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797932","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-07","<p>We do not hold this information.</p><p> </p><p>Energy suppliers have their own individual systems and criteria for recording offers for installations of a smart meter.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797932/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T10:38:20.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797932/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797932/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-30","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many homes will have been offered a smart meter by the end of 2017.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","116839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797933","Department of Health","false","2017-12-05","<p>We recognise the important role that the European Medicines Agency plays in the protection of human and animal health.</p><p> </p><p>In the negotiations the Government will discuss with the European Union and Member States how best to continue cooperation in the field of medicines regulation in the best interests of both the United Kingdom and the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is fully committed to continuing the close working relationship with our European partners. Our aim is to ensure that patients in the UK and across the EU continue to be able to access the best and most innovative medicines and be assured that their safety is protected through the strongest regulatory framework and sharing of data. As the Prime Minister has stated, we want deep, broad and dynamic co-operation and in this context, the UK would like to find a way to continue to collaborate with the EU, in the interests of public health and safety.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797933/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T16:45:42.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797933/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797933/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-30","European Medicines Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what his policy is on the UK's relationaship with the European Medicines Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","116840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797934","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-07","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>No estimate has been made.</p><p> </p><p>Suppliers are mandated by government to offer every household and small business in Great Britain a smart meter by 2020, and Ofgem are regulating them against this requirement.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797934/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T10:40:39.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797934/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797934/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-30","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the difference between the number of homes that will have been offered a smart meter by end of 2020 and the number of meters that will be installed by that date.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","116841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797935","Department for Education","false","2017-12-08","<p>The Department is aware of concerns raised regarding the level of fees charged by some agencies when offering a supply teacher permanent employment. Whilst there are no immediate plans to legislate in this area, the Department is working with Crown Commercial Service to develop a new commercial framework for schools aimed at bringing consistency and transparency of cost to this area.</p><p> </p><p>The new arrangement will address inconsistent practices of some agencies and the levels of mark-up charged as well as the issue of finders’ fees. It is anticipated that the new commercial deal will be available for use by schools from September 2018.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797935/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-08T14:08:50.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797935/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797935/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-30","Supply Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will bring forward legislation to ban finders fees being imposed by teaching supply agencies where a school seeks to appoint on a permanent basis a supply teacher originally provided by those agencies.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","116842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797936","Department of Health","false","2017-12-05","<p>As shown by the exciting new industry commitments announced in a Life Sciences Sector Deal as part of the Industrial Strategy White Paper published on 27 November, the United Kingdom remains a uniquely globally attractive environment for investment, research and innovation and will continue to thrive after European Union exit.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797936/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-05T16:52:47.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797936/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797936/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-30","Life Sciences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what new opportunities will be available to the life sciences sector after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","116843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797937","Department for Education","false","2017-12-08","<p>The Department is aware of concerns raised regarding the behaviour of some agencies when dealing with schools as well as the level of costs charged. Whilst there are no immediate plans to legislate in this area, the Department is working with Crown Commercial Service to develop a new commercial framework for schools aimed at bringing consistency and transparency of cost to this area.</p><p> </p><p>The new arrangement will address inconsistent practices of some agencies and the levels of mark-up charged as well as the level of fees charged. It is anticipated that the new commercial deal will be available for use by schools from September 2018.</p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li></li></ul>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797937/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-08T14:05:47.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797937/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797937/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-30","Supply Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will bring forward proposals regulate teaching supply agencies and cap costs charged for the provision of supply teachers.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","116844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797938","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-07","<p>This is not a new levy. The exemption for eligible energy intensive industries from up to 85% of the Contract-for-Difference supplier obligation is not a low carbon electricity levy and therefore not under scope of the Control for Low Carbon Levies.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797938/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-07T16:17:46.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797938/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797938/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-30","Energy Intensive Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the levy established to support energy intensive industries through the Electricity Supplier Obligations (Amended and Excluded Electricity) (Amendment) Regulations 2017 will count as a new levy under the terms of the Control for Low Carbon Levies.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","116845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797939","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-08","<p>The regulations were laid before Parliament on 1 December 2017. The Approved Driving Instructor Part 3 test will be implemented from 23 December 2017.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797939/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-08T11:26:58.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797939/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797939/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-30","Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the new Approved Driving Instructor Part 3 Test will be introduced.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","116846"
